## 🔑 Brodmann Areas — Key Regions

| Brodmann Area(s) | Location | Primary Function |
|-----------------|----------|-----------------|
| **4** | Precentral gyrus | **Primary motor cortex (M1)**; voluntary movement; corticospinal origin; somatotopic (motor homunculus) |
| **6** | Premotor cortex + SMA (mesial surface) | Motor planning, preparation, and sequencing; mirror neurons (premotor); SMA: internally generated movement, bimanual coordination |
| **3a / 3b / 1 / 2** | Postcentral gyrus | **Primary somatosensory cortex (S1)**; 3a: proprioception; 3b: cutaneous; 1: texture; 2: size/shape |
| **5** | Superior parietal lobule | Somatosensory association; limb position; sensorimotor integration |
| **7** | Superior/inferior parietal lobule | Visuospatial integration; multimodal; spatial attention; contralateral neglect if damaged |
| **17** | Calcarine sulcus banks | **Primary visual cortex (V1/striate cortex)**; retinotopic; lower field → upper bank; macula represented posteriorly; V1 input to layers IVCα/β |
| **18 / 19** | Occipital association cortex | V2, V3, V4 (color), V5/MT (motion) — ventral and dorsal visual streams |
| **41 / 42** | Superior temporal gyrus (Heschl's gyri) | **Primary auditory cortex (A1)**; tonotopic; bilateral; within lateral sulcus |
| **22** | Superior temporal gyrus (posterior) | **Wernicke's area** (dominant hemisphere); auditory language comprehension |
| **44 / 45** | Inferior frontal gyrus (pars opercularis/triangularis) | **Broca's area** (dominant hemisphere); speech production; syntactic processing |
| **39** | Angular gyrus (inferior parietal) | Reading, writing, arithmetic; cross-modal integration; dominant: Gerstmann's syndrome if damaged |
| **40** | Supramarginal gyrus (inferior parietal) | Phonological processing; tactile discrimination; conduction aphasia (arcuate fasciculus) |
| **9 / 46** | Dorsolateral prefrontal cortex (DLPFC) | Working memory, executive function, cognitive flexibility, planning |
| **10** | Frontopolar cortex | Prospective memory; multitasking; rostral PFC functions |
| **11 / 13** | Orbitofrontal cortex (OFC) | Reward valuation; impulse control; emotional regulation |
| **24 / 32 / 25** | Anterior cingulate cortex (ACC) | Error monitoring; conflict detection (dorsal); mood/autonomic (ventral); area 25 = subgenual ACC (depression target) |
| **23 / 31** | Posterior cingulate cortex (PCC) | Autobiographical memory; default mode network; self-referential processing |

