## 🔑 Cortical Development and Plasticity

### Corticogenesis (Inside-Out Pattern)
| Feature | Detail |
|---------|--------|
| **Inside-out pattern** | Deep cortical layers (VI, V) born first; superficial layers (II, III) born last |
| **Progenitor cells** | Ventricular zone (VZ) → neuroepithelial cells → radial glia; subventricular zone (SVZ) → basal progenitors |
| **Radial migration** | Postmitotic neurons migrate along radial glial fibers from VZ to cortical plate (Reelin signaling essential) |
| **Critical periods** | Windows of heightened plasticity when sensory experience shapes cortical circuits; V1 ocular dominance critical period: 4–8 years human |
| **Cortical malformations** | Lissencephaly (failed migration → smooth brain); pachygyria (broad gyri); polymicrogyria (many small gyri); focal cortical dysplasia (local abnormality → epilepsy) |

### Adult Cortical Plasticity
| Phenomenon | Example | Mechanism |
|-----------|---------|-----------|
| **Use-dependent expansion** | Violin players: enlarged right-hand digit cortex; Braille readers: enlarged fingertip cortex | LTP-like changes; axonal sprouting |
| **Post-injury reorganization** | After limb amputation → phantom limb; adjacent cortex expands into denervated territory | Unmasking of latent horizontal connections; LTP |
| **Hebbian plasticity** | Frequently used synapses strengthen; unused synapses weaken | LTP/LTD; spine morphology changes |

